      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) is a commercially validated code with documented V&V history. Version control, regression testing, and release notes confirm software quality assurance at the required gradation for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions and benchmark test cases from ASME V&V 20 were used to verify the numerical implementation of the Navier-Stokes solver and the hemolysis power-law transport equation. Results confirm correct code behavior within expected tolerances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation was applied across three systematically refined meshes (coarse: 1.2 M cells, medium: 4.8 M cells, fine: 19.2 M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) for normalized index of hemolysis was 3.1%, within the 5% threshold for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate 5 L/min, pressure rise 270 mmHg, blood analog viscosity 3.5 cP at 37°C) are documented in the FDA benchmark dataset. Boundary conditions in the CFD model replicate these conditions with less than 2% deviation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against five independent laboratory measurements from the FDA benchmark study. Mean absolute percentage error was 8.4%, within the 15% acceptance band established for MRL 2 hemolysis predictions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest — normalized index of hemolysis — is directly linked to the clinical safety endpoint of red blood cell damage. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress distribution, scalar stress exposure) are established surrogates in the hemolysis literature and are relevant to identifying worst-case operating conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry operating within the CPB flow-pressure envelope. The validation scenario covers the same pump class, fluid properties, and operating regime as the intended use, supporting adequate relevance at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 given the use of a commercially verified solver with documented iterative convergence controls.",
      "rationale": "Iterative residuals were monitored to 1e-6 for all transport equations; no additional solver error quantification is mandated at MRL 2 for this factor. Factor is scoped as not-assessed consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; standard operating procedures and analyst training records are maintained but not formally scored.",
      "rationale": "Simulation analysts followed documented SOPs for mesh generation, boundary condition setup, and post-processing. Formal use-error scoring is not required at MRL 2 for this device class."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection is documented in the simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) was selected based on published literature and FDA guidance. Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2 for Class II CPB devices."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; input parameter values are traceable to published material property sources.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog density and viscosity values are sourced from ASTM F1841. Hemolysis model constants are taken from Giersiepen et al. (1990). Formal input uncertainty propagation is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; experimental sample provenance is documented in the FDA benchmark dataset metadata.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark experimental data includes five laboratory replicates. Statistical characterization of sample variability beyond what is reported in the benchmark dataset is not required at MRL 2."
    },
